Jaco Henning, of Ogallala, finishes the C-4 District meet at West Winds Golf Course in Ogallala on Thursday. (Andrew Bottrell / The North Platte Telegraph) Shields 1st, Henning 2nd in Cross Country district meets 
JohnMark Shields, of Lexington, sprints towards the finish line of the B-4 District meet at West Winds Golf Course in Ogallala on Thursday. (Andrew Bottrell / The North Platte Telegraph) Posted: Thursday, October 15, 2015 10:43 pm Shields 1st, Henning 2nd in Cross Country district meets By Andrew Bottrell abottrell@nptelegraph.com nptelegraph.com 
OGALLALA — Lexington’s JohnMark Shields took home a district title, and a pair of Ogallala runners notched top three finishes at the B-4 and C-4 district meets at West Winds Golf Course on Thursday. 
Shields out-sprinted Joshua Hergenreder, of Scottsbluff, to the line for first place in the B-4 meet. Shields finished with a time of 16 minutes, 15.5 seconds, three seconds faster than Hergenreder. The top 15 runners, and top three teams, each qualified for the state championships at Kearney Country Club on Oct. 23.     Subscription required
